cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use O1-O in research, please cite it as below."
title: "O1-O: A Deterministic Code Synthesis Operator with an Algebraic Type System, a 7-Pass Causal Knowledge Inference Engine, and an Autonomous Engagement Pipeline"
authors:
  - family-names: "Foss"
    given-names: "David Tom"
    email: "dtfoss-dev@proton.me"
date-released: "2026-06-26"
version: "1.0.0"
license: "Apache-2.0"
repository-code: "https://github.com/DT-Foss/O1-O"
type: software
abstract: >
  O1-O is a deterministic code synthesis system that composes working programs
  from natural-language intent without any LLM in the generation loop.
  Composition is performed by a closed-set 8-color algebraic type system over
  ~1245 verified code fragments; the knowledge layer is a binary .causal graph
  format (132 domain files) traversed by a 7-pass deterministic inference engine
  (exact-chain, semantic-direction, fuzzy-match, analogical, cross-domain,
  contextual, recombination). Every generated artifact passes a seven-layer
  verification pipeline (compile, structural intent, property-based, algebraic,
  symbolic execution, taint analysis, logic-consistency). The system is paired
  with an autonomous nine-phase engagement operator that orchestrates the full
  platform end-to-end from a single IP address. The codebase is fully air-gap
  capable: AES-256-CTR (PBKDF2 600k) and PE/ELF/Mach-O parsers are implemented
  from scratch in the Python standard library; only msgpack, jellyfish, requests
  and beautifulsoup4 are external dependencies. Builds on prior work in
  programming-language theory (Curry-Howard correspondence, typed lambda
  calculus), causal knowledge graphs (peer-reviewed across 9 papers accepted
  at 4 international IEEE 2026 conferences — IEEE ICECET 2026 hosted by
  Medipol University in Rome, IEEE-NANO 2026 in Nanjing as the flagship
  conference of the IEEE Nanotechnology Council, IEEE IRI 2026 hosted by
  the University of Washington Bothell in Seattle, and NURER 2026 in Almaty
  organized in cooperation with the International Atomic Energy Agency —
  plus a bit-perfect IBM z/OS mainframe security assessment validated on
  real z15 hardware), and a self-extending closed-loop architecture in which the
  system detects its own knowledge gaps, generates tasks against them, and
  folds successful patterns back into the knowledge graph deterministically.
keywords:
  - deterministic code synthesis
  - program synthesis
  - causal knowledge graph
  - algebraic type system
  - formal verification
  - self-improving systems
  - autonomous code generation
  - air-gapped computing
  - sovereign software
